{{FUN-top}}
A Trainz '''Asset''' is a self-defining collection of mutually supporting more elementary data types that are usually used alone or in some cases, are used as an accessory in conjunction with other Assets to be rendered by the game software into a realistic 3D model of some sort and degree.

When an asset is a sub-component (a wheel type making part of a bogey or truck), it is usually set off inside a {{TR|C|p=container}} which will likely define other information about how the asset is used by the larger asset. Thus assets can greatly differ both in complexity and size, generality and specificity. Consider the many shapes on a steam locomotive and each part that moves independent of others. Each group will likely have component assets, and the complicated whole is made up of building blocks small asset by small asset.

Further, Assets can range from a sound or HTML data file providing background (one as 'realism' or color, the other as a instruction in a game {{TL|Driver}} {{TL|Session}}), a texture used to fill in the surface color and surface effects of a {{wp|polygon mesh}}, the mesh itself, or an aggregate of several or many sub-components, like the obvious kinds of rolling stock. But assets also include buildings, trackside related objects such as signals, relay boxes, {{TG|S|junction switches}} (points) and switch motors or switch levers.
{{Trainz-stub}}
