==The Setting (Year 1945, Hiroshima)==
# Barefoot Gen starts with an air strike by American bombers. # The father refuses to be trained because he knows it is meaningless; he thinks Japanese cannot win with bamboo sticks while Americans are using machineguns and other firearms. # The father is arrested due to his refusal of training and is beaten. # Gen’s family gets in trouble because people are hostile to anti-war ideas. # Gen bites off fingers of the chairman and his son. # Gen’s sister is stripped because she is accused of stealing money. # Mr.Pak shares his valuable bowl of rice. # Gen’s father scolds his children several times (Respect for Koreans and so on) # Gen’s elder brother goes to war in order to take honor back to his family. # Gen’s elder brother goes to training camp - one of his teammates commit suicide after continuous excessive trainings. He realizes the war is really wrong. # Gen and Shinji disguises as beggars to help their family financially # Gen breaks glasses in order to support the owner of glass-house, and receives a toy battleship as a gift. Gen gives the battleship to his younger brother. # Enola Gay drops an atomic bomb called Little Boy in 8:15, 6th August, 1945. # Gen witnesses the horror and devastation caused by the atomic bomb. # Despite all the difficulties that occurred, Gen saves the chairman and his son # Gen and his mother survive, but the rest of the family burns alive because they could not escape from a collapsed building. # After witnessing the excruciating death of the family members, the mother loses her sanity. # With the help of Mr. Pak, Gen is able to safely evacuate him and his mother from the burning buildings # Instantly after the bombing, Gen’s mother gives a birth # Gen helps bring up his sister # The volume ends with a intense scene: the newborn witnesses the grievous scene of the bombing, vowed not to tolerate any further tragic affairs.
