==Order Hymenophyllales==
The order '''{{fny-w|Hymenophyllales}}''' contains a single family, the {{fny-w|Hymenophyllaceae}}, or filmy fern family.  In New York, only one species of this family has been verified as living outside of cultivation, and that species is considered to be endangered in the state.

===Family Hymenophyllaceae===

The only member of the '''Hymenophyllaceae''' found in New York is a gametophitic weft fern ''Crepidomanes intricatum'', which was transferred from '''''Trichomanes''''' to the mostly Asian '''''Crepidomanes''''' genus in 2011.

{{fny-table|Hymenophyllaceae
}}
{{fny-genus|Crepidomanes|Grotto felt|1135|1|
}}
{{fny-species
| species = Crepidomanes intricatum
| author1 = (Farrar) Ebihara & Weakley (2011)
| syn1    = Trichomanes intricatum ''Farrar''
| en1     = Appalachian trichomanes
| en2     = Filmy fern
| en3     = Weft fern
| status  = Native
| status1 = Endangered
| ref-11  = {{fny-nyfa|1609|1|}}
| ref-12  = {{fny-nrcs|TRIN13|N0|NY: Endangered}}
| ref-21  = DEC-A<ref name=DECA>{{fny-ref|DECA}}</ref>
| fna-id  = 233501311
| i-tsn   = 507540
| note    = <ref>''Crepidomanes intricatum'' is assumed to be gametophitic only. Sporophitic generations of this plant have not been observed. The species was tranferred from ''Trichomanes'' by [http://www.naturalheritage.com/!UserFiles/WebContent/Publications/weakley_witsell_etal_vascular_flora_2011.pdf Ebihara & Weakley (2011)] based on molecular sequence.</ref>
| map     = Crepidomanes intricatum nymap.svg
