==Order Salviniales==

The order '''{{fny-w|Salviniales}}''' (the heterosporous or water ferns) contains the families {{fny-w|Salviniaceae}} (mosquitoferns) and {{fny-w|Marsileaceae}} (waterferns), which have few species represented in New York.

===Family Salviniaceae===

The family {{fny-w|Salviniaceae}} contains the aquatic fern genera ''Azolla'' and ''Salvinia''.  Though ''Azolla'' has previously been placed in its own family, the {{fny-w|Azollaceae}}.

{{fny-table|Salviniaceae|
}}
