=== Operators ===

Now, a program that just prints out text isn't very useful. To make a program that is useful we will need to learn a few more things about Lua. One of these things is the concept of ''operators''. An operator is something that takes one or two values, does some work on them, and produces a new value. For example, in Lua we have the <code>+</code> operator, which takes two numbers, adds them together, and produces their sum.

{{Code:Lua
| code =
= 2 + 2
| output =
4
}}

Lua also has the <code>-</code> operator, which subtracts one number from another; the <code>*</code> operator, which multiplies two numbers; and the <code>/</code> operator, which divides one number by another.  

{{Code:Lua
| code =
= 100 - 50
| output =
50
}}

{{Code:Lua
| code =
= 5 * 4
| output =
20
}}

{{Code:Lua
| code =
= 10 / 2
| output =
5
}}

One operator that you may find very useful is the <code>..</code> operator. This is the ''concatenation'' operator, which takes two strings (two bits of text) and joins them together.

{{Code:Lua
| code =
= "Hello, " .. "Fred!"
| output =
Hello, Fred!
}}
